menu "DALI Driver"

    config DALI_RX_GPIO
        int "DALI RX GPIO number"
        range 0 48
        default 5
        help
            GPIO number connected to the DALI bus receive line.

    config DALI_TX_GPIO
        int "DALI TX GPIO number"
        range 0 48
        default 6
        help
            GPIO number connected to the DALI bus transmit line.

    config DALI_TX_INVERT
        bool "Invert TX signal polarity"
        default n
        help
            Enable this option when the hardware circuit between the MCU TX GPIO
            and the DALI bus performs an odd number of signal inversions.

            When enabled the RMT symbol levels are flipped so that the DALI bus
            still sees the correct Manchester-encoded waveform.

            NOTE: do NOT use flags.invert_out for this purpose -- that flag also
            inverts the RMT idle level between frames, which would pull the DALI
            bus low during inter-frame gaps and corrupt the protocol timing.

            Leave disabled (default) when the circuit is non-inverting or performs
            an even number of inversions (e.g. two back-to-back transistor stages).

    config DALI_RX_INVERT
        bool "Invert RX signal polarity"
        default n
        help
            Enable this option when the hardware circuit between the DALI bus and
            the MCU RX GPIO performs an odd number of signal inversions.

            When enabled the RMT RX channel's input-inversion flag is set so that
            the driver sees the correct Manchester-encoded levels regardless of the
            hardware polarity.

            Leave disabled (default) when the circuit is non-inverting or performs
            an even number of inversions.

endmenu
